First, we solve the equation $4x = 3y$ for $x$ to express it in terms of $y$.
\begin{align*}
4x &= 3y \\
x &= \frac{3}{4}y
\end{align*}
Next, we substitute this expression for $x$ into the expression $\frac{2x+y}{3x-2y}$.
\begin{align*}
\frac{2x+y}{3x-2y} &= \frac{2\left(\frac{3}{4}y\right)+y}{3\left(\frac{3}{4}y\right)-2y} \\
&= \frac{\frac{3}{2}y+y}{\frac{9}{4}y-2y} \\
&= \frac{\frac{5}{2}y}{\frac{1}{4}y} \\
&= \frac{5}{2} \cdot \frac{4}{1} \\
&= \frac{5\cdot 4}{2\cdot 1} \\
&= \frac{20}{2} \\
&= \boxed{10}
\end{align*}
The answer is: 10
